column12: Tape printing apparatus and tape holding case
column13: A tape printing apparatus (2) is arranged to be used with a tape holding case (8). The tape holding case holds a supply of image receiving tape (28) and a supply of laminating tape (48). An opening (49) is provided between the two tape supplies. A printing mechanism (4) is arranged to print an image on the image receiving tape as it traverses the opening (49). A cutting location is provided where the image receiving tape is cut an image has been printed thereon. The cutting location and printing mechanism (4) lie on opposite sides of the first and second tape supplies.

column12: Tape printing apparatus and tape holding case having cooperative surface
column13: A tape printing apparatus arranged to be used with a tape holding case. The case holds a first supply of image receiving tape and a second supply of laminating tape. An opening is provided between the first and second tape supplies. A printing mechanism is arranged to print an image onto the image receiving tape as it traverses the opening. A cutting location is provided where the image receiving tape is cut after an image has been printed thereon. The cutting location and printing mechanism lie on opposite sides of the first and second tape supplies.

column12: Data structure for improved software implementation of a neural network
column13: A data structure for processing a neural network, and a method of processing a neural network are disclosed. The data structure, which is in a memory device, includes a first data structure portion and a second data structure portion within the memory device. The first data structure portion includes a first plurality of sequential memory locations. Each of the first plurality of sequential memory locations stores a respective input data signal value to be provided to respective inputs of both a first neuron and a second neuron of a first layer of the neural network. The second data structure portion includes a second plurality of sequential memory locations. Each of the second plurality of sequential memory locations stores a respective weight value corresponding to a respective input of a respective one of the first neuron and the second neuron.

column12: Tape holding case
column13: A tape holding case (14) for use with tape printing apparatus has a housing defining a cavity in which is located a supply (16) of image receiving tape (2) having a heat sensitive layer. The housing is constructed in a light tight manner to prevent exposure of the heat sensitive layer to light prior to formation of an image thereon. The light-tightness of the case may be maintained by a pivoted door (24), which is pivoted when the case is inserted into the printing apparatus.

column12: LIGHT-PROOF CARTRIDGE AND TAPE PRINTING DEVICE
column13: The invention relates to a tape cartridge (14, 60) for use in a tape printing device (38) having an interior space in which is placed a supply (16) of take-up tape (2) with a thermosensitive coating (12). It is proposed that the tape cartridge (14, 60) should be made light-proof, in order to prevent light from affecting the thermosensitive coating (12) before an image is printed upon it. Furthermore, a tape printing device (38) is disclosed which has a space (66) for a tape cartridge (14, 60) and comprises a removable light-proof tape cartridge (14, 60) located in this space (66) having a supply (16) of take-up tape (2) with a thermosensitive coating (12) and a printing unit for printing an image on to the take-up tape (2) which directly and specifically conveys heat to the take-up tape (2) in order to print the image upon it.

column12: MEMS device and process
column13: A MEMS transducer such as a microphone has a membrane and a membrane electrode forming a two-layer structure. The membrane electrode is in the form of a lattice of conductive material with holes, the pitch and/or size of the lattice holes varying from a central region of the membrane electrode to a region laterally outside the central region. The ratio of conductive material to the openings thus decreases from the centre to the sides of the transducer. The openings may be circular or polygonal. The membrane may be a crystalline material such as silicon nitride and the electrode may be aluminium, aluminium-silicon alloy or titanium nitride. The transducer may alternatively be a capacitive sensor.

column13: An active selective headset system characterized by a headset (51) having controller means (50) with an LMS adapter, feedback compensator and cancellation filter with reference microphone (54) and residual microphones (53) and speakers (52), where the controller means synthesizes an 'anti-noise' to cancel the noise before reaching the ear canal. column12: Apparatus for and methods of damage repair
column13: Apparatus is disclosed for repairing a flaw in a surface, particularly in the field of vehicle glass repair. The apparatus has a housing adapted to engage the surface to be repaired, a repair seal for sealing between the housing and around the flaw to be repaired to define a repair space over the flaw. A reservoir communicates with the repair space and, in use, contains liquid repair material. A vacuum pump communicates with the repair space and the reservoir to apply a partial vacuum to the repair space and to the reservoir without repair liquid from the reservoir being drawn into the repair space in order to degas separately the flaw and repair liquid in the reservoir. After appropriate degassing, repair liquid from the reservoir is caused to flow into the repair space to fill the repair space with repair liquid.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR PRODUCING HYDROCARBONS
column13: A method and apparatus for producing hydrocarbons from a well that has a production string positioned within a casing string. A progressive cavity pump is provided that has a rotor, a stator, an inlet in fluid communication with the hydrocarbon producing formation, and an outlet in fluid communication with the production string. The well is stimulated by reciprocating the stator of the progressive cavity pump along the rotor and relative to the casing string while operating the progressive cavity pump, stimulating the well.

column12: IMPROVEMENT IN APPARATUS FOR AND METHODS OF DAMAGE REPAIR
column13: A találmány egyrészt berendezés felületben lévő hiba (31) javítására,amely berendezés tartalmaz a felülethez való csatlakoztatásra alkalmasházat, a felület és a ház között a hiba (31) fölötti javítási teret(65) meghatározó javítási tömítést a ház és a javítandó hiba (31)környezete közötti tömítéshez, valamint a javítási térrel (65)kapcsolatban álló és arra részleges vákuumot kialakító elsővákuumeszközt. A berendezést az jellemzi, hogy tartalmaz a javításitérre (65) növelt vákuumot alkalmazó második vákuumeszközt, valamint ajavítási térre (65) javítási folyadékot juttató tárolót. A találmánymásrészt flexibilis folt (60) felületen lévő hiba (31) javításáraszolgáló berendezéssel való alkalmazáshoz, amely berendezésselfolyékony javítási anyag (86) van a hiba (31) környezetében lévő,részben kiürített javítási térbe (65) bevezetve, ahol a folt (60) gázés folyadék számára áteresztő lap anyagból van és egyik oldalánragasztógyűrűvel rendelkezik a felületre a javítandó hiba (31) körülvaló tapadáshoz, ahol a folt (60) tartalmaz benne kialakított legalábbegy bevágást a ragasztógyűrűben, hogy lehetővé tegye a bevágásonkeresztül a folyadék vagy gáz áthaladását. A találmány továbbá eljárásfelületben lévő hiba (31) javítására, amelynek során a hiba (31)környezetében javítási teret (65) alakítanak ki, a javítási térre(65), egy, a javítási teret (65) körülvevő gyűrű alakú tartományra ésfolyékony javítási anyagra (86) részleges vákuumot alkalmaznak,mialatt a folyékony javítási anyagot (86) a javítási téren (65) kívültartják, a javítási térre (65) növelt vákuumot alkalmaznak, afolyékony javítási anyagot (86) a javítási térbe (65) bevezetik, ajavítási térre (65) alkalmazott vákuumot eltávolítják és a teretezután nyomás alá helyezik, a javítási teret (65) körülvevő gyűrűalakú tartományból a részleges vákuumot eltávolítják és a javításiteret (65) nyomástalanítják, valamint a folyékony javítási anyag (86)keményedésig való megkötése után a javított felületet simítják. column12: IMPROVEMENT IN APPARATUS FOR AND METHODS OF DAMAGE REPAIR
column13: Apparatus (10) is disclosed for repairing a flaw (31) in a surface (30), particularly in the field of vehicle glass repair. The apparatus has a housing (11) adapted to engage the surface to be repaired, a repair seal for sealing between the housing (11) and around the flaw (31) to be repaired to define a repair space (65) over the flaw. A reservoir communicates with the repair space (65) and, in use, contains liquid repair material (86). A vacuum pump communicates with the repair space (65) and the reservoir to apply a partial vacuum to the repair space (65) and to the reservoir without repair liquid (86) from the reservoir being drawn into the repair space (65) in order to degas separately the flaw (31) and repair liquid (86) in the reservoir. After appropriate degassing, repair liquid (86) from the reservoir is caused to flow into the repair space (65) to fill the repair space with repair liquid.

column12: Aparelho para reparar um defeito em uma superfìcie, remendo flexìvel e método de reparar um defeito em uma superfìcie
column13: "APARELHO PARA REPARAR UM DEFEITO EM UMA SUPERFìCIE, REMENDO FLEXìVEL E MéTODO DE REPARAR UM DEFEITO EM UMA SUPERFìCIE". Trata-se de um aparelho (10) para reparar um defeito (31) em uma superfície (30), particularmente no campo do reparo de vidros de veículos. O aparelho tem um invólucro (11) adaptado para acoplar a superfície a ser reparada, uma vedação de reparo para a vedação entre o invólucro (11) e ao redor do defeito (31) a ser reparado, para definir um espaço de reparo (65) sobre o defeito. Um reservatório se comunica com o espaço de reparo (65) e, em uso, contém o material líquido do reparo (86). Uma bomba de vácuo se comunica com o espaço de reparo (65), e o reservatório para aplicar um vácuo parcial ao espaço de reparo (65) e ao reservatório sem que o líquido de reparo (86) seja extraído para o espaço de reparo (65) a fim de desgaseificar separadamente o defeito (31) e o líquido de reparo (86) no reservatório. Depois da desgaseificação apropriada, o líquido de reparo (86) do reservatório é encaminhado para o espaço de reparo (65) para preencher o espaço de reparo com o líquido de reparo.

column12: Anordning og fremgangsmate for reparasjon av en skade i en overflate
column13: Anordning (10) for reparasjon av en skade (31) i en overflate (30), særlig på området reparasjon av kjøretøyglass. Anordning omfatter et hus (11) innrettet til anlegg mot overflaten som skal repareres, en reparasjonstetning for å tette mellom huset (11) og rundt skaden (31) som skal repareres, for å avgrense et reparasjonsrom (65) over skaden. Et reservoar kommuniserer med reparasjonsrommet (65) og inneholder, under bruk, flytende reparasjonsmateriale (86). En vakuumpumpe kommuniserer med reparasjonsrommet (65) for utøvelse av delvis vakuum i reparasjonsrommet (65) og reservoaret uten at reparasjonsvæske (86) fra reservoaret suges inn i reparasjonsstedet (65), for separat å fjerne gass fra skaden (31) og reparasjonsvæsken (86) i reservoaret. Etter tilfredsstillende fjernelse av gass påvirkes reparasjonsvæsken (86) fra reservoaret til å strømme inn i reparasjonsrommet (65) for å fylle dette med reparasjonsvæske.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR PRODUCING HYDROCARBONS
column13: A method and apparatus for producing hydrocarbons from a well that has a production string positioned within a casing string. A progressive cavity pump is provided that has a rotor, a stator, an inlet in fluid communication with the hydrocarbon producing formation, and an outlet in fluid communication with the production string. The well is stimulated by reciprocating the stator of the progressive cavity pump along the rotor and relative to the casing string while operating the progressive cavity pump, stimulating the well.

column12: Sports paddle with improved head portion
column13: A sports paddle including a head portion coupled to a handle portion. The head portion includes at least one core layer positioned between first and second face plates. The first and second face plates have first and second outer surfaces, respectively. The head portion defines a plurality of through-head portion holes extending from the first outer surface to the second outer surface and a plurality of grooves extending into the first and second face plates. The head portion can include first and second face plates having first and second outer surfaces, respectively, and the handle portion can include a grip. Each of the first and second outer surfaces can include a roughened region and a generally smooth region. The smooth region of the first outer surface can space apart the grip from the roughened region of the first outer surface.
column15: KAPHEIM ROBERT T;;DOYLE SCOTT M;;GRAHAM TERRI R

column12: Patch for repair of damaged glass
column13: Apparatus is disclosed for repairing a flaw in a surface, particularly in the field of vehicle glass repair. The apparatus has a housing adapted to engage the surface to be repaired, a repair seal for sealing between the housing and around the flaw to be repaired to define a repair space over the flaw. A reservoir communicates with the repair space and, in use, contains liquid repair material. A vacuum pump communicates with the repair space and the reservoir to apply a partial vacuum to the repair space and to the reservoir without repair liquid from the reservoir being drawn into the repair space in order to degas separately the flaw and repair liquid in the reservoir. After appropriate degassing, repair liquid from the reservoir is caused to flow into the repair space to fill the repair space with repair liquid.

column12: UN APARATO Y UN METODO PARA REPARAR UN DEFECTO EN UNA SUPERFICIE Y UN PARCHE FLEXIBLE PARA SER UTILIZADO CON UN APARATO PARA REPARAR UN DEFECTO UN EN UNA SUPERFICIE
column13: Se divulga un aparato y un método para reparar un defecto en una superficie, particularmente en el campo de la reparacion de vidrios de los vehículos. El aparato posee una carcasa adaptada para incluir la superficie a reparar, un sellado de reparacion para sellar el espacio entre la carcasa y alrededor del defecto a reparar, a fin de definir un espacio de reparacion sobre el defecto. Un reservorio se comunica con el espacio de reparacion y , durante el uso, contiene el material de reparacion líquido. Una bomba de vacío se comunica con el espacio de reparacion y el reservorio para aplicar un vacío parcial al espacio de reparacion y al reservorio, sin que el líquido de reparacion sea impulsado desde el reservorio hacia adentro del espacio de reparacion a fin de desgasificar en forma separada el defecto y el líquido de reparacion en el reservorio. Luego de una desgasificacion apropiada, el líquido de reparacion proveniente del reservorio es encausado para fluir hacia el espacio de reparacion y llenar el espacio de reparacion con el líquido de reparacion. También se divulga un parche flexible para ser utilizado con el aparato.

column12: BRIDGING MEMBER FOR CONCRETE FORM WALLS
column13: A building component having first and second high density foam panels and improved bridging members for connecting the panels that extend between and may be molded into the panels. The bridging members include a pair of elongated end plates oriented in a top to bottom direction of the panels, a pair of substantially identical web members joining the end plates and being substantially symmetrically disposed above and below a central horizontal axis of the bridging member, and a pair of strip members oriented in the top to bottom direction of the panels intersecting the web members. The web members have a unique configuration that maximizes load bearing capacity with a minimum amount of material. The strip members may abut against and be substantially flush with respective inner surfaces of the foam panels to assist in positioning and forming the panels during molding. Seating areas for positioning horizontally and/or vertically disposed rebar in predetermined positions are also provided.

column12: Pulsed-Multiline Excitation for Color-Blind Fluorescence Detection
column13: The present invention provides a technology called Pulse-Multiline Excitation or PME. This technology provides a novel approach to fluorescence detection with application for high-throughput identification of informative SNPs, which could lead to more accurate diagnosis of inherited disease, better prognosis of risk susceptibilities, or identification of sporadic mutations. The PME technology has two main advantages that significantly increase fluorescence sensitivity: (1) optimal excitation of all fluorophores in the genomic assay and (2) “color-blind” detection, which collects considerably more light than standard wavelength resolved detection. Successful implementation of the PME technology will have broad application for routine usage in clinical diagnostics, forensics, and general sequencing methodologies and will have the capability, flexibility, and portability of targeted sequence variation assays for a large majority of the population.

column12: Glass repair device
column13: Apparatus for the repair of flaws in a surface, particularly conical chips 31 in vehicle windscreens 30, provides for spatially separate degassing of the flaw and the repair liquid 86. A housing engages the surface and isolates a repair space via a seal 16. The repair liquid is held in a separate reservoir 80, connected via conduit 93 to the repair space. A vacuum creating means is connected to both volumes. Repair liquid may be supplied in a capsule for insertion into holder 81 and released by engagement with a spike (91, figure 4). The housing may define two concentric chambers connected by a valve (15, figure 2), the outer delimited by seal 14 and the inner by seal 16. Piston 40 is used to improve the evacuation of the repair space and then to pressurise it. The extreme positions of the piston are indicated by the engagement of a pin, mounted in the wall of the piston bore 41, with a cam track on the external surface of the piston (figures 11 and 12).

column12: Bridging member for concrete form walls
column13: A building component having first and second high density foam panels and improved bridging members for connecting the panels that extend between and may be molded into the panels. The bridging members include a pair of elongated end plates oriented in a top to bottom direction of the panels, a pair of substantially identical web members joining the end plates and being substantially symmetrically disposed above and below a central horizontal axis of the bridging member, and a pair of strip members oriented in the top to bottom direction of the panels intersecting the web members. The web members have a unique configuration that maximizes load bearing capacity with a minimum amount of material. The strip members may abut against and be substantially flush with respective inner surfaces of the foam panels to assist in positioning and forming the panels during molding. Seating areas for positioning horizontally and/or vertically disposed rebar in predetermined positions are also provided.

column12: PULSED-MULTILINE EXCITATION FOR COLOR-BLIND FLUORESCENCE DETECTION
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a technology called Pulse-Multiline Excitation or PME.

SOLUTION: A pulse-multiline excitation apparatus for analyzing a sample containing one or more fluorescent species includes: one or more lasers configured to emit two or more excitation lines, having different wavelengths respectively; a timing circuit coupled to the one or more lasers and configured to generate the two or more excitation lines sequentially according to a timing program to produce time-correlated fluorescence emission signals from the sample; a non-dispersive detector positioned to collect the time-correlated fluorescence emission signals emanating from the sample; and an analyzer coupled to the detector and configured to associate the time-correlated fluorescence emission signals with the timing program to identify constituents of the sample.

column12: ENSEMBLE AUXILIAIRE POUR DISJONCTEUR EN BOITIER MOULE
column13:
Un ensemble intégré de protection 10 est un disjoncteur qui comporte un dispositif de base pour la protection contre les surcharges en même temps que des accessoires électriques sélectifs. Un couvercle 13 d'accès aux accessoires en matériau plastique moulé, fixé au couvercle 12 de l'ensemble intégré de protection, protège les composants des accessoires que renferme le couvercle du disjoncteur contre l'environnement. La combinaison d'un dispositif de commande de déclenchement pour surcharge et d'un ensemble auxiliaire peut être montée sur place dans l'ensemble intégré de protection.

Application aux disjoncteurs en boîtier moulé.

column12: METHOD FOR SUPPORTING A SLOW WAVE CIRCUIT VIA AN ARRAY OF DIELECTRIC POSTS
column13: A slow wave circuit is supported within a surrounding metallic barrel portion of a traveling wave tube via the intermediary of an array of dielectric posts each of which is brazed at one end to the slow wave circuit and at the other end to the barrel. During fabrication of the tube, the post structures are first bonded to a metallic strip which in turn is bonded to the inside of the barrel. The strip preferably has a coefficient of thermal expansion equal to that of the dielectric posts.

column12: PULSED-MULTILINE EXCITATION METHOD FOR COLOR-BLIND FLUORESCENCE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a technology called pulse-multiline excitation or PME, and achieve a novel approach to fluorescence detection with application for high-throughput identification of informative SNPs, which could lead to more accurate diagnosis of inherited disease, better prognosis of risk susceptibilities, or identification of sporadic mutations.

SOLUTION: The PME technology has two main advantages that significantly increase the fluorescence sensitivity: (1) optimal excitation of all fluorophores in the genomic assay and (2) "color-blind" detection, which collects considerably more light than standard wavelength resolved detection. This technology is extremely different from a conventional DNA sequencing instrument characterized by single light source excitation and chromatic dispersion for DNA sequence identification. Implementation of the PME technology has broad application for routine usage in clinical diagnostics, forensics, and general sequencing methodologies, and has the capability, flexibility, and portability of targeted sequence variation assays for a large majority of the population.

column12: METHOD FOR REMOVAL OF FOULING FROM A PIPELINE
column13: A method for removing fouling from a pipeline includes determining the location of fouling in the pipeline. Once determined, the method further includes installing a hot tap in the pipeline. A flex conduit is inserted into the pipeline through the hot tap and a treatment fluid is flowed into the pipeline through the conduit. The treatment fluid is used to remove the fouling from the pipeline. Once the fouling is sufficiently removed, the flexible conduit is removed from the pipeline.

column12: Pulsed-multiline excitation for color-blind fluorescence detection
column13: The present invention provides a technology called Pulse-Multiline Excitation or PME. This technology provides a novel approach to fluorescence detection with application for high-throughput identification of informative SNPs, which could lead to more accurate diagnosis of inherited disease, better prognosis of risk susceptibilities, or identification of sporadic mutations. The PME technology has two main advantages that significantly increase fluorescence sensitivity: (1) optimal excitation of all fluorophores in the genomic assay and (2) “color-blind” detection, which collects considerably more light than standard wavelength resolved detection. Successful implementation of the PME technology will have broad application for routine usage in clinical diagnostics, forensics, and general sequencing methodologies and will have the capability, flexibility, and portability of targeted sequence variation assays for a large majority of the population.

column13: MOLDED CASE CIRCUIT BREAKER MULTIPLE ACCESSORY UNIT An integrated protection unit is a circuit breaker which includes basic overcurrent protection facility along with selective electrical accessories. column12: DISPOSITIF DE COMMANDE DE DECLENCHEMENT ENSEMBLE AUXILIAIRE POUR DISJONCTEUR EN BOITIER MOULE
column13:
Un ensemble intégré de protection est un disjoncteur 10 qui comporte un dispositif de base de protection contre les surcharges en même temps que des composants auxiliaires électriques sélectifs. Un couvercle 13 en matériau plastique moulé permettant d'accéder aux composants auxiliaires est fixé au couvercle 12 de l'ensemble intégré de protection et protège les composants auxiliaires contre l'environnement. La combinaison d'un dispositif de commande du déclenchement en cas de surcharge et d'un ensemble auxiliaire peut être installée sur place à l'intérieur de l'ensemble intégré de protection. Cette combinaison comporte les circuits électroniques de commande des composants auxiliaires ainsi que les composants mécaniques de déclenchement et de réarmement.

column12: NON-INVASIVE NERVE ACTIVATOR WITH ADAPTIVE CIRCUIT
column13: A topical nerve activation patch includes a flexible substrate, a dermis conforming bottom surface of the substrate comprising adhesive and adapted to contact a dermis of a user, a flexible top outer surface of the substrate approximately parallel to the bottom surface, a plurality of electrodes positioned on the patch proximal to the bottom surface and located beneath the top outer surface and coupled to the flexible substrate, a power source, and electronic circuitry that generates an output voltage applied to the electrodes. The electronic circuitry includes a controller, a voltage monitoring circuit coupled to the controller, a current monitoring circuit coupled to the controller, a switch coupled to the controller and a boosted voltage circuit coupled to the switch and the power source.

column12: RESOURCE MANAGEMENT
column13: Among other things, receiving a description of an amount of resources from an initiating party; receiving a set of proposals from the initiating party, each proposal having a cost that is less than or equal to the amount of resources, the set having a total cost that is greater than the amount of resources; displaying a selected proposal from the set of proposals to a target party; receiving an acceptance of the selected proposal from the target party; and reducing the amount of resources by an amount equal to the cost of the selected proposal. Also, identifying a budget, identifying a group of proposals, each proposal having a cost and an associated target party; routing a proposal in the group to the proposal's associated target party; in response to an acceptance of the proposal, reducing the budget by an amount equal to the cost of the proposal.

column12: System and Method for Operating a Point-of-Sale (POS) System in a Retail Environment
column13: A self-checkout (SCO) terminal in a retail store controls banks of lights to communicate context information to a customer in order to better inform them about various events. column12: A MACHINE FOR FORMING A CONTAINER FROM A BLANK OF SHEET MATERIAL
column13: A machine for forming a container from a blank of sheet material is provided. The machine includes a first forming module and a second forming module that is movable with respect to the first forming module for adjusting a width of said forming assembly. Each forming module includes a top clamp configured to move in a substantially vertical direction to engage the blank, a major flap folder configured to move in a substantially vertical direction, and an entrance plow configured to direct the blank into the forming assembly. The machine further includes first and second minor flap folders that are extendable inwardly toward the blank along a substantially straight path. The first minor flap folder is positioned near the first forming module, and the second minor flap folder is positioned near the second forming module. A method for forming the container from the blank using the machine is also provided.

column12: Estrutura de instrumento agrìcola, e, tubo de elevação para a estrutura principal de um instrumento agrìcola
column13: "ESTRUTURA DE INSTRUMENTO AGRìCOLA, E, TUBO DE ELEVAçãO PARA A ESTRUTURA PRINCIPAL DE UM INSTRUMENTO AGRìCOLA". Uma estrutura de instrumento agrícola de elevação e rotação compreende uma estrutura principal, tendo um tubo de elevação e uma estrutura portadora montada no tubo de elevação. O tubo de elevação compreende um tubo de suporte principal que se estende verticalmente, tendo superfícies planas e uma luva exterior resistente à corrosão. A luva exterior resistente à corrosão compreende placas resistentes à corrosão, correspondentes às superfícies planas do tubo de suporte principal. Cada uma das placas possui uma superfície interior e uma superfície exterior. Pelo menos, uma das placas resistentes à corrosão se liga a uma outra placa. Uma das placas de ligação é dotada de uma saliência que se estende até depois da superfície exterior da outra placado par. As placas são soldadas no canto a uma outra, entre a saliência e a outra placa. As placas são também dotadas de aberturas oblongas, tendo bordas oblongas. As bordas oblongas são soldadas no canto ao tubo de suporte principal de forma a acoplarem a luva ao tubo de suporte principal.
column15: GRAHAM WILLIAM DOUGLAS;;MCCARTNEY SCOTT CHARLES;;SMITH WILLIAM HOWARD;;BUCKLEY PATRICK M;;BENNETT ROBERT EDWIN

column12: Lift tube for an agricultural implement frame
column13: A lift and rotate agricultural implement frame comprises a main frame having a lift tube and a carrier frame slidably mounted to the lift tube. The lift tube comprises a vertically extending main support tube having planar surfaces and a corrosion resistant exterior sleeve. The corrosion resistant exterior sleeve comprises corrosion resistant plates corresponding to the planar surfaces of the main support tube. Each of the plates has an interior surface and an exterior surface. At least one of the corrosion resistant plates adjoins another plate. One of the adjoining plates is provided with an overhang that extends past the exterior surface of the other plate of the pair. The plates are fillet welded to one another between the overhang and the other plate. The plates are also provided with oblong openings having oblong edges. The oblong edges are fillet welded to the main support tube to couple the sleeve to the main support tube.
column15: GRAHAM WILLIAM DOUGLAS;;MCCARTNEY SCOTT CHARLES;;SMITH WILLIAM HOWARD;;BUCKLEY PATRICK M;;BENNETT ROBERT EDWIN

column12: CHASSIS OF AN AGRICULTURAL MACHINE
column13: The invention relates to a chassis (14) of an agricultural machine, comprising a main frame (22) and a lifting tube (26) which extends upwards from the main frame (22). Said lifting tube comprises a main carrier tube (50) and a corrosion-proof sheath (52), said sheath (52) surrounding the main carrier tube (50) and comprising a plurality of plates (56, 58, 60, 62). A carrier frame (30) is mounted on the lifting tube in a movable manner, and can be pivoted about a vertical pivoting axis between a transport position and a working position. A first plate (56) is provided with a projecting area (68) which extends beyond the outer surface (66) of a second plate (58) which is adjacent to said first plate (56). A fillet weld (70) is carried out between the projecting area (68) of the first plate (56) and the second plate (58), fixing the first plate (56) and the second plate (58) together.

A fillet weld (70) is carried out between the projecting area (68) of the first plate (56) and the second plate (58), fixing the first plate (56) and the second plate (58) together.

column12: MOLDED CASE CIRCUIT INTERRUPTER RATING PLUG KEYING AND INTERLOCK ARRANGEMENT
column13: An electronic circuit interrupter includes an electronic trip circuit contained within a circuit interrupter enclosure along with an externally accessible rating plug for setting the ampere rating. The rating plug includes keying tabs that fit within corresponding keying slots formed on the top surface of the electronic circuit interrupter enclosure. Interlock is provided between the rating plug and the electric panelboard which includes a plurality of electronic circuit interrupters connected within an industrial power system. Tabs formed on the side walls of the rating plug are trapped under the panelboard face plate to prevent removal of the rating plug without first removing the panelboard face plate.

column12: Molded case circuit breaker actuator-accessory unit

column12: LIFT TUBE FOR AN AGRICULTURAL IMPLEMENT FRAME
column13: A lift and rotate agricultural implement frame comprises a main frame having a lift tube and a carrier frame slidably mounted to the lift tube. The lift tube comprises a vertically extending main support tube having planar surfaces and a corrosion resistant exterior sleeve. The corrosion resistant exterior sleeve comprises corrosion resistan t plates corresponding to the planar surfaces of the main support tube. Each of the plates has an interior surface and an exterior surface. At least one of the corrosion resistant plates adjoins another plate. One of the adjoining plates is provided with an overhang that extends past the exterior surface of the other plate of the pair. The plates are fillet welded to one another between the overhang and the other plate. The plates are also provided with oblong openings having oblong edges. The oblong edges are fillet welded to the main support tube to couple the sleeve to the main support tube.

column12: Modular artillery charge system
column13: A modular artillery charge system consists of two distinct solid propellant harge modules. Each module consists of a three-piece combustible cartridge case design and bi-directional center core core ignition system. The three-piece combustible cartridge case consists of a combustible case body, having an open end and a end; a cap, having a closed end and an open end; and a center tube. The closed ends of the body and the cap have a hole in the center. The center core tube is positioned longitudinally through the combustible case body, and contacts the closed ends of both the cap and the body. The bi-directional center core ignition system comprises a core igniter bag and two end igniter bags. The core igniter bag occupies the center core tube, and the end igniter bags contact the core igniter bag. The bi-directional center core ignition system may be ignited by percussion primers or a laser ignition system. The first module is used individually or in groups of two. The second module is used in groups of three or more. The modules are not used with one another. The modules are distinguishable by color and by shape, so that the modules may be distinguished even under conditions of complete darkness. Each module has a coating applied to the exterior of the case, and mylar seals over the ends, to provide protection to and from the environment.

column12: Stress relief system and splice module for inserted cables
column13: A stress relief system and splice module for an inserted cable, the stress relief system having a main housing with an opening and a series of beveled features and a series of serrations on an inner surface. The system also has a rotating collar having an opening aligned with the opening of the main housing. The rotating shaft ring has a series of driven features configured to be inserted into the opening of the main housing such that when the rotating shaft ring is rotated relative to the main housing, the driven features cooperate with the ramp features to compress the inserted cable with the stress relief system. The rotational collar also has at least one ratchet tab configured to mate with a series of serrations of the main housing to provide a ratchet function between the rotational collar and the outer housing. The splicing module comprises the stress relieving system.

column12: NON-INVASIVE NERVE STIMULATION
column13: One example provides a nerve stimulation treatment using electrodes coupled to a user. Examples determine a target charge level and output a series of pulses from the electrodes. For each pulse outputted, examples measure a charge value of the pulse and compare the charge value to the target charge level. If the charge value is greater than the target charge level, examples reduce a strength level of a subsequent outputted pulse. If the charge value is less than the target charge level, examples increase the strength level of a subsequent outputted pulse.

column13: A topical nerve stimulator patch and system are provided including a dermal patch; an electrical signal generator associated with the patch; a signal receiver to activate the electrical signal generator; a power source for the electrical signal generator associated with the patch; an electrical signal activation device; and a nerve feedback sensor.

column12: Computer game with replaceable character heads
column13: A computer program displays a virtual environment and a character in the virtual environment. The character includes a body and a replaceable head. Player control signals from an input device control replacement of the character's replaceable head and other character actions in the virtual environment. The computer program may attribute play characteristics to the character based on the head in place on the character at a given time. These characteristics may be thematically consistent with the displayed appearance of the head in place. The program may allow a player to select a set of character heads for use with the character. The program may allow the player to collect heads from the virtual environment and store the collected heads for use. The program may offer communication with other connected computer systems facilitating a multi-player or on-line interact hosted game.

column12: 적응형 회로를 구비한 비침습성 신경 활성화기
column13: 국소 신경 활성화 패치는 가요성 기판, 접착제를 포함하고 사용자의 진피와 접촉하도록 구성된 상기 기판의 진피 등각-형성 하부 표면, 하부 표면에 대략 평행한 기판의 가요성 상부 외측 표면, 복수의 전극이 위치됨을 포함한다. 하부 표면에 근접한 패치 상에 위치하고 상부 외측 표면 아래에 놓이며 가요성 기판에 결합되는 복수의 전극, 및 상기 전극에 인가된 출력 전압을 생성하는 전자 회로를 포함한다. 상기 전자 회로는 제어기, 제어기에 결합된 전압 모니터링 회로, 제어기에 결합된 전류 모니터링 회로, 제어기에 결합된 스위치, 및 스위치 및 전원에 결합된 승압 전압 회로를 포함한다.

column13: A topical nerve activation patch includes a flexible substrate, a dermis conforming bottom surface of the substrate comprising adhesive and adapted to contact a dermis of a user, a flexible top outer surface of the substrate approximately parallel to the bottom surface, a plurality of electrodes positioned on the patch proximal to the bottom surface and located beneath the top outer surface and coupled to the flexible substrate, a power source, and electronic circuitry that generates an output voltage applied to the electrodes. The electronic circuitry includes a controller, a voltage monitoring circuit coupled to the controller, a current monitoring circuit coupled to the controller, a switch coupled to the controller and a boosted voltage circuit coupled to the switch and the power source.

column12: Non-invasive nerve stimulation
column13: One example provides a nerve stimulation treatment using electrodes coupled to a user. Examples determine a target charge level and output a series of pulses from the electrodes. For each pulse outputted, examples measure a charge value of the pulse and compare the charge value to the target charge level. If the charge value is greater than the target charge level, examples reduce a strength level of a subsequent outputted pulse. If the charge value is less than the target charge level, examples increase the strength level of a subsequent outputted pulse.

column12: MACHINE AND METHOD FOR FORMING REINFORCED POLYGONAL CONTAINERS FROM BLANKS
column13: A machine for forming a container from a blank of sheet material is provided. The blank includes a reinforcing panel assembly for forming a reinforcing corner assembly. The machine includes a hopper station for storing the blank in a substantially flat configuration and a forming station for forming the blank into the container. The forming station includes an initial forming station that rotates a first portion of the reinforcing panel assembly with respect to a second portion of the reinforcing panel assembly, and a secondary forming station having male and female forming members with shapes corresponding to an interior shape and an exterior shape of the reinforcing corner assembly, respectively. The male and the female forming members are configured to form the reinforcing corner assembly by compressing together the first and second portions of the reinforcing panel assembly.
column15: AGANOVIC AMER;;GRAHAM THOMAS DEAN;;SMITH KENNETH CHARLES;;CONLEY JOHN HERSHCEL;;TEANY ROBERT BRADLEY;;GULIK GREGORY SCOTT;;SPURLOCK PAUL ANDREW

The male and the female forming members are configured to form the reinforcing corner assembly by compressing together the first and second portions of the reinforcing panel assembly.

column12: COMPUTING SYSTEM HAVING FAULT CONTAINMENT
column13: A multi-processor, shared memory computing system is disclosed. The system comprises a plurality of processing element modules, input/output processor modu les and shared memory modules interconnected with the processing elements and input/outp ut processors. The modules are interconnected by point to multi-point communication links. Each module has one transmit port and a plurality of receive ports interconnecte d through the links with transmit ports of other modules. Shared memory is updated and rea d by exchanging frames forming memory access transactions over these links. Between f rames, idle codes are broadcast across the links. In response to locally sensing a fail ure at a module, a failed module modifies its idle code to reflect the failure. Interconn ected modules lock-out a failed module in response to sensing an inhibit-on idle code at the receive ports. This facilitates the isolation and containment of faulty modules.

column12: SAATSYSTEM
column13: Eine Produktverteilungsanlage umfasst eine bedarfsgerechte Produkt-Aufnahmeanordnung mit einem Trichter. Der Trichter ist so konfiguriert, dass ein Luftstrom, der in die Aufnahmeanordnung fließt, das Produkt dahinein mit sich führt und das Produkt durch eine Vielzahl von Leitungen weitertransportiert. Die Produktverteilungsanlage umfasst ferner einen Behälter zum Aufbewahren des Produkts vor der Bereitstellung des Produkts an die Aufnahmeanordnung und eine Dosier- und Förderanlage, die so konfiguriert ist, dass sie das Produkt von dem Behälter zum Aufnahmeanordnungs-Trichter bewegt, so dass eine Produktmenge größer als eine vorbestimmte Menge während des Betriebs des Systems in dem Aufnahmeanordnungs-Trichter vorgehalten wird.

column12: MACHINE AND METHOD FOR FORMING REINFORCED POLYGONAL CONTAINERS
column13: A machine for forming a container from a blank of sheet material includes a forming station and a compression station. The forming station is configured to form a reinforcing corner assembly from first and second reinforcing panels extending from an end panel of the blank. The compression station is configured to rotate side panels and end panels of the blank to be substantially perpendicular to a bottom panel of the blank. The compression station includes a plurality of plows at least partially defining a plunger opening, and a plunger vertically movable through the plunger opening. The plurality of plows are configured to rotate the side panels and the end panels towards the interior surface of the bottom panel.

column12: Máquina e método para formar um recipiente a partir de um bloco bruto de material de chapa
column13: máquina e método para conformar recipientes poligonais reforçados. trata-se de uma máquina para conformar um recipiente a partir de um bloco bruto de material de chapa que inclui uma estação de conformação e uma estação de compressão. a estação de conformação é configurada para conformar uma montagem de canto de reforço a partir do primeiro e do segundo painéis de reforço que se estendem a partir de um painel de extremidade do bloco bruto. a estação de compressão é configurada para girar os painéis laterais e painéis de extremidade do bloco bruto para ficarem substancialmente perpendiculares a um painel de fundo do bloco bruto. a estação de compressão inclui uma pluralidade de pás que define pelo menos parcialmente uma abertura de êmbolo e um êmbolo móvel de modo vertical através da abertura de êmbolo. a pluralidade de pás é configurada para girar os painéis laterais e os painéis de extremidade em direção à superfície interior do painel de fundo.

column13: resumo patente de invenção: para "máquina e método para conformar recipientes poligonais reforçados". trata-se de uma máquina para conformar um recipiente a partir de um bloco bruto de material de chapa que inclui uma estação de conformação e uma estação de compressão. a estação de conformação é configurada para conformar uma montagem de canto de reforço a partir do primeiro e do segundo painéis de reforço que se estendem a partir de um painel de extremidade do bloco bruto. a estação de compressão é configurada para girar os painéis laterais e painéis de extremidade do bloco bruto para ficarem substancialmente perpendiculares a um painel de fundo do bloco bruto. a estação de compressão inclui uma pluralidade de pás que define pelo menos parcialmente uma abertura de êmbolo e um êmbolo móvel de modo vertical através da abertura de êmbolo. a pluralidade de pás é configurada para girar os painéis laterais e os painéis de extremidade em direção à superfície interior do painel de fundo.

column12: FORMING REINFORCED POLYGONAL CONTAINERS MACHINE AND METHOD
column13: A machine for forming a container from a blank of sheet material includes a forming station and a compression station. The forming station is configured to form a reinforcing corner assembly from first and second reinforcing panels extending from an end panel of the blank. The compression station is configured to rotate side panels and end panels of the blank to be substantially perpendicular to a bottom panel of the blank. The compression station includes a plurality of plows at least partially defining a plunger opening, and a plunger vertically movable through the plunger opening. The plurality of plows are configured to rotate the side panels and the end panels towards the interior surface of the bottom panel.

column12: ELECTROREFINING PROCESS FOR SEPARATING METALS
column13: The invention comprises an electrorefining process for separating a metal from a composition including the said metal, the method comprising forming an electrorefining cell having an anode, a cathode and an electrolyte, wherein the anode comprises the metal and the electrolyte comprises a substance which is liquid at its operating temperature and at this temperature is comprises wholly or largely of ionic species, and applying a sufficient potential difference between the anode and the cathode to cause the metal to transfer from the anode to the cathode and to be deposited thereon, wherein gap between the anode and the cathode is minimised, the electrolyte is circulated at high velocity through the cell, and the available surface area of the cathode is maximised by providing the metal in a form which has a large surface area per unit volume. In preferred embodiments, either the anode is in the form of a basket, and the metal composition is provided in a finely divided form within the said basket or the metal composition is provided in the form of a long, thin rod which itself forms the anode. Preferably, the composition including the metal comprises spent nuclear fuel, and the electrolyte comprises an ionic liquid.

column12: Method of mapping multiple address spaces into single PCI bus
column13: A method and apparatus are provided for mapping multiple address spaces into a single bus, such as a single peripheral component interconnect (PCI) bus. The single bus is coupled to a first processor complex and a second processor complex. An original address of a memory access is shifted to a unique address space for each originator/target of an operation. The shifted address is used on the single bus. Then the shifted address is shifted back to the original address for completing the operation on a destination bus. The original address of a memory access is shifted to a unique address space for each originator/target of an operation using a respective predefined value (X1, X2, or X3) for shifting the original address above a predefined boundary for each originator/target of the operation. Shifting back the shifted address to the original address for completing the operation on the destination bus uses a respective predefined value (X1, X2, or X3) for the shifted back address to the original address for completing the operation on the destination bus. Using the shifted address on the single bus utilizes a dual address cycle (DAC) of the single bus for the shifted address. Completing the operation on a destination bus utilizes a single address cycle (SAC) of the destination bus for the shifted back address to the original address.

column12: Rivet dispensing systems and methods of use thereof
column13: Rivet dispenser systems and methods of use thereof are provided. In a non-limiting embodiment, the rivet dispenser system comprises a rivet receiving member defining a channel therein, and a seat member. The channel includes a curved region. The rivet receiving member comprises a first port and a second port. The first port communicates with the channel and is configured to receive rivets. The second port communicates with the channel and is configured to dispense rivets. The channel extends between the first port and the second port and is configured to transport rivets from the first port to the second port in a series arrangement and in a preselected orientation. The seat member communicates with the second port and is configured to selectively engage with a rivet holder of a resistance spot rivet welding apparatus and introduce a single rivet to the rivet holder at one time.

column12: 리벳 분배 시스템 및 이의 사용 방법
column13: 리벳 디스펜서 시스템 및 이의 사용 방법이 제공된다. 비한정적인 구현예에서, 리벳 분배기 시스템은 채널을 그 안에 정의하는 리벳 수용 부재, 및 안착 부재를 포함한다. 채널은 만곡 영역을 포함한다. 리벳 수용 부재는 제1 포트와 제2 포트를 포함한다. 제1 포트는 채널과 연통하고, 리벳을 수용하도록 구성된다. 제2 포트는 채널과 연통하고, 리벳을 분배하도록 구성된다. 채널은 제1 포트와 제2 포트 사이에서 연장되고, 제1 포트에서 제2 포트까지 직렬 배열 및 미리 선택된 배향으로 리벳을 운송하도록 구성된다. 상기 안착 부재는 제2 포트와 연통하고, 저항 스폿 리벳 용접 장치의 리벳 홀더와 선택적으로 맞물려 한 번에 하나의 리벳을 리벳 홀더에 도입하도록 구성된다.

column12: Wireless communication features for respiratory protection devices
column13: The invention provides a breathing apparatus and system, and specifically provides a breathing apparatus that can be used with a plurality of removable electrical functional components that are wirelessly communicable with other devices. In one embodiment, a breathing apparatus includes: a body, at least a portion of the body defining a volume; a mask communication unit (MCU) located at least partially within the volume; at least one electrical functional component, the at least one electrical functional component being in communication with the MCU; and a rechargeable power source located at least partially within the volume, the rechargeable power source providing power to each of the at least one electrical functional component.

column12: HAIR COLORING METHODS AND COMPOSITIONS THEREOF
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide hair coloring methods, compositions thereof, and kits thereof, for providing similar final coloring results over the entire hair length from the roots to the tips.SOLUTION: A method comprises the steps of: i) mixing a developer component with a dye component to obtain a non-diluted hair coloring composition, wherein the developer component comprises an oxidizing agent and the dye component comprises at least one oxidative dye precursor and/or an alkalizing agent; ii) applying a first portion of the non-diluted hair coloring composition to the hair, preferably to the hair roots, and retaining a second portion of the non-diluted hair coloring composition; iii) mixing the second portion with a diluent component comprising water and optionally at least one active component, at a mixing ratio of 4:1 to 1:2 to obtain a diluted hair coloring composition; iv) applying the diluted hair coloring composition to the hair, preferably to the hair lengths and tips; and v) rinsing the hair.SELECTED DRAWING: None

column13: The present invention provides methods of determining a survival predictor score of a subject having mantle cell lymphoma (MCL). column32: ROSENWALD A ET AL: "THE PROLIFERATION GENE EXPRESSION SIGNATURE IS A QUANTITATIVE INTEGRATOR OF ONCOGENIC EVENTS THAT PREDICTS SURVIVAL IN MANTLE CELL LYMPHOMA", CANCER CELL, CELL PRESS, US, vol. 3, no. 2, 1 February 2003 (2003-02-01), pages 185 - 197, XP001191077, ISSN: 1535-6108, DOI: 10.1016/S1535-6108(03)00028-X

column12: EVALUATION OF MANTLE CELL LYMPHOMA AND METHODS RELATED THERETO
column13: The present invention provides methods of determining a survival predictor score of a subject having mantle cell lymphoma (MCL). The present invention also provides methods of predicting the survival outcome of a subject having MCL and provides methods of selecting a treatment for a subject having MCL.

column12: Evaluación del linfoma de células del manto y procedimientos relacionados con el mismo
column13: Un procedimiento para predecir el resultado de supervivencia de un sujeto humano que tiene linfoma de células del manto (LCM), cuyo procedimiento comprende: (1) determinar una puntuación del indicador predictivo de supervivencia del sujeto (a) aislando el producto de expresión génica de ARN de una muestra de biopsia fijada con formol e incluida en parafina (FFPE) del sujeto; (b) obteniendo datos de expresión génica del producto de expresión génica de ARN, en el que los datos de expresión génica comprenden valores de señal que representan niveles de expresión para cada gen de la tabla 1; y (c) determinando una puntuación del indicador predictivo de supervivencia a partir de los datos de expresión génica, en el que la puntuación del indicador predictivo de supervivencia se determina calculando un producto de multiplicación para cada gen de la tabla 1, en el que el producto de multiplicación es el producto matemático de la transformación logarítmica del valor de señal de un gen y un valor de coeficiente para ese gen, el valor del coeficiente para el gen enumerado en la tabla 1, y sumando los productos de la multiplicación; y (2) clasificar al sujeto como perteneciente a uno de los siguientes grupos en base a la puntuación del indicador predictivo de supervivencia: (i) buen pronóstico, (ii) pronóstico intermedio y (iii) mal pronóstico.
